items.name: Emma Watson (JG)
items.description:
A commission of @Springbok707.

Emma Watson is a British actress who needs no introduction. For this embedding, the original idea was to capture her 2010 looks, with that famous pixie haircut.

Update: I've now updated the TI to look more like nowadays Emma. Version 2.0 is step 125 of a TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

If you want to help me keep creating TIs, please consider buying me a coffee.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (emm4w4ts0n:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description: Retrained with a new dataset of 15 images. This version should look more like nowadays Emma.

modelVersions.name: v1.0 (2010 version)
modelVersions.description: 1500-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

modelVersions.name: v0.1 (2010 version)
modelVersions.description: This isn't the first time I publish a 100-step version... but it certainly isn't usual. I was really surprised during training by how good the image that the AI generated for step 100 looked, so after publishing the TI I decided to test it... And it doesn't look half bad! I'm publishing it more like a curio than anything, cause it's pretty obvious it still needed more training by then. If someone can offer some insights as to why the AI learnt this subject so fast, I'd love to read about it. Just to be clear, the TI was trained under the name "3mwatson2010", so I guess there's no way the AI can relate the vectors of "Emma Watson" already present in the database with the ones that were being trained for this TI. But maybe I'm wrong about that...

items.name: Camouflage Uniform
items.description:
Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

To support me you can buy me a coffe at https://ko-fi.com/antonioriolo

Training settings:

34 images, 20 steps, 10 epochs, you find many epochs (with test images using plot xy script) on my Patreon while supporting me.

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras (Recommended for best quality, you may try other samplers)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 10

  • LORA weight for txt2img: reccomended 0.2-0.7.

  • Keys: wearing camouflage_uniform, wearing cap, holding a rifle, military camp, in a forest

This model i think it's a masterpiece, i really like it!!

I advice to use 0.3-0.5 as model weight.

About the main keyword "wearing camouflage_uniform" it might not be necessary, but i used it in all prompts, sometime giving to it a bigger weight.

"wearing cap" really doesn't need a weight, just use it as you want whenever you want the woman with a cap.

"holding rifle" might need an higher weight to work, i used 1.5 in my prompts. And anyway when you use this keyword be prepared to generate a lot of images before finding one that makes sense.

"military camp" and "in a forest" are just to get an image in the proper environment.

Also, as you can see from my images i have generated these uniforms in different colors, in this case, since all training images are black and green you might need to bet in SD creativity for the result and my advice is to give a very high weight to the color, like "(wearing camouflage_uniform:1.3), wearing cap, (holding a rifle:1.5), (red uniform:1.5)"

It works also with anime, i used Chillout for realistic one and Yesmix for anime ones.

I'm uploading epoch 4 out of 10, the one that gived best results with images with holding a rifle keyword (hardest image to generate). If you want to try and experience all of them come in my Patreon.

Enjoy!

If you'd like to support my efforts and have access to early and bleeding edge builds, please think about joining my Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/betterCuteAsians

items.name: SXZ Texture Bringer [ Concept ]
items.description:
All the content I make is and will be completely free on CivitAI.
But if you want to support me with a coin, then you can do it here.

Sample images was generated with 🌕Luma.

PLEASE MAKE SURE THAT YOUR LORA FILENAME MATCHES LORA NAME IN PROMPT.

How to use:

Your prompt should be not too complicated. Shorter = better. Trigger words is wowtexture of. Also i highly recommed to use this structure:
wowtexture of YOUR SURFACE, YOUR PROMPT, seamless

Nice to know:

Generated textures aren't 100% tiled or seamless, so sometimes you need to improve it manually.

Tag seamless increases a chance of seamless result, so your prompt SHOULD end with it, if you want as much seamless as it possible.

Also, i beg you to DESCRIBE NOT AN OBJECTS BUT SURFACES, cause if you go with object description you will get not a texture at all, so please use it correctly.

Strength 0.8 is optimal.

Recommended settings:
Clip Skip 2
VAE: kl-f8-anime2
Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras or DPM++ 2M alt Karras
ENSD: 31337
Hires.fix: x1.5 and higher
Upscaler: 4x UltraSharp, 4x Valar or any like (Denoising strenght 0.5)

Enjoy and share your feedback.

items.name: Charlotte Stokely
items.description:
📝Biography 📝

🌟Charlotte Stokely 🌟

A retired American model and TV actress was born as Brittney Vitale on August 8, 1986 in Salt Lake City, Utah. She first started modelling and performing at age 19. Stokely has also modelled for American Apparel and appeared in mainstream films and TV shows. She has modelled for several American Apparel advertisements, and even caught the attention of Dov Charney, the company's founder and CEO. Charney was a fan of her work and asked her to come in for some test shots. Stokely has also appeared uncredited in the 2009 comedy film Black Dynamite and starred in the 2014 TV movie Eve's Secret. She was a contestant on the reality television show Jenna's American Sex Star and has also appeared on the TV series Submission.

Stokely's career in the adult entertainment industry has not been without controversy. Despite this, Stokely has become a popular figure in the industry, earning a nomination for Best New Starlet at the AVN Awards in 2007. Stokely is 5'3" tall and has blonde hair, blue eyes, and a slim build with an incredibly rotund butt, with measurements of 34B-24-36.

💡Generation Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling 🔧

  • Most images have been generated with Lora weighted between 1 - 1.25.

  • All example images have been done with CyberRealistic v1.4.

  • If doing a portrait headshot, to maintain the model's face during a hi-res fix, it is best to use 8x NMKD Faces upscaler at ~0.15 denoise strength. The higher you go the more clarity but the more prone to lose accuracy.

🚀Upscaling🚀

  • Ultimate SD upscale script used for all upscales ~.15 - .4 denoising using 8x NMKD Faces or 4X UltraSharp redraw upscalers.

  • The closer the face (or larger the image), the lower the denoise should be set to prevent "oddities".

  • Expand your tile width/height, mask blur and padding respectively the larger you scale your image.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • Doing these LARAs are forcing me to get my prompt game tight. 👌😎

  • Leave a review if you liked it.

  • Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond.

items.description:
If you like my contributions to the community, please consider Buying Me A Coffee or check out my other sites on AllMyLinks

TRAINING INFO

  • Trained on 17 photos (face only)

  • Trained at 768 resolution, so 768x768 inpainting works great.

RECOMMENDED SETTINGS

The training images used were cropped in from shitty early 2000's dslr's, so image quality wasn't great. I recommend using 'restore faces' but in your auto1111 settings, lower the restore faces strength to something like 0.7-0.8 which makes the effect less than the default setting of 0.5.

For txt2img, a weight of 0.7-0.9 will give a little more flexibility, but 1.0 isn't bad. A weight of 1.0 works really well for inpainting.

GETTING THE BEST LIKENESS WITH LORA'S

The checkpoint you use can heavily influence the likeness of a celebrity Lora. I train my Lora's on SD15, so you'll get the best likeness on any model that used SD15 as the base model. See this example for how a checkpoint can influence the look of a Lora.

items.description:
2023/4/30 update

Fix the compatibility problem induced by VAE.

Introduction

A LoRA model of Serval Landau from Honkai: Star Rail. The trigger tag is 'serval landau'. The key features are 'blonde hair, long hair, streaked hair, black choker, jacket, gloves'. The 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) are recommended. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.6 version (original) YesMix.

Cautions (Must Read)

For anime model,

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

  • Some preview images are generated using 'Hires Fix' and upscaled using 'SD Upscale'. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

  • The maximum of generating resolution should not exceed 1024 theoretically, otherwise extra/deformed head/limbs will be waiting for you :). Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: Oshino Ougi (Monogatari)
items.description:
Lora model of Oshino Ougi from Monogatari series. Previews were made with weight 1.0.

Best spooky boogie :D This model still have some minor issues so I might still come back to it - a bit irritating really, because I tried to troubleshoot all the problems and make it perfect, but then new problems started to appear >_> I guess it's still the usual quality, but I was hoping to best myself.

Prompts:

  • Usual outfit - oshino ougi, black undershirt, pink shirt, black necktie, puffy sleeves, sleeves past fingers, pleated skirt, black pantyhose, loafers

  • Male uniform - oshino ougi, gakuran, black jacket, black gloves, black pants

  • Black dress - oshino ougi, colored inner hair, bare shoulders, black bowtie, black dress, elbow gloves, two-sided skirt, black thighhighs

Tips and tricks:

  • half-closed eyes - for getting the squinted look, through it can sometimes result in completely closed eyes.

  • Male uniform have pants in it because that's how it's supposed to be and it comes out ok, but in my datatset it was always pleated skirt, black pantyhose so you can use that instead.

  • Better to prompt 1girl always, even with male uniform.

  • colored inner hair works maybe 1/3 of time, extra weight helps and sometimes red hair can help too.

  • If black dress ends up with straps instead of halterneck, it's probably best to put cleavage into negative.

items.name: Syroh Style
items.description:
Syroh Style

Greetings everyone, I am excited to share with you my first LoRA (Low Rank Adaptation) project. For this endeavor, I utilized a set of 30 images created by the talented artist Syroh 🌟大阪こみトレ - pixiv (Heavy NSFW Warning) as the basis for training the LoRA model.

Usage

I highly recommend utilizing the LoRA algorithm with weight values ranging from 0.7 to 0.8. I have observed that using weights of 0.85 or higher tends to result in excessively rendered facial features, while weights below 0.6 fail to adequately capture the desired Syroh style.

This particular model demonstrated compatibility with several other LoRA-friendly models. Therefore, you may exercise discretion when selecting the appropriate model for your needs.

Please note that the trigger word for this model is "Syroh."

I have conducted thorough testing on my personal, non-publicly available model. Unfortunately, I am unable to provide direct links. However, I have included images below for your reference

It is worth mentioning that this LoRA model exhibits a predisposition towards catgirls. This can be attributed to Syroh's strong inclination for drawing catgirls, resulting in a dataset that primarily comprises such images. Regardless, I trust you will find my LoRA model satisfactory. Please feel free to share any feedback or raise any queries you may have.

If you liked that LoRA, feel free to check out my other LoRA JTVeemo Style - v1.0 | Stable Diffusion LoRA | Civitai.

Thank you!

Experimental lora based on just 9 arts! The official arts that represent this or that skin are taken only from modern arts, I did not touch the old ones. The resolution of all art is widescreen, so I advise you to use a resolution of 768x512 (and upscale, how to do this is written below)

If you want to support me, then you can subscribe to my Patreon and get builds earlier than they come out here (versions on patreon will always be newer by one than here) This will help me a lot in updating the video card over time to make models even better and faster (the main thing is better)

just use hires fix as much as your video card is capable of, so as not to give an error, with 8gb of video memory it is 512x768 with hires fix 2-2.15, upscaler Latent (nearest-exact), the picture will be much more detailed. If you want a style close to the original but with more detail, don't use Denoising strength above 0.6, but to avoid artifacts, do not use too low a value, optimally 0.5

LORA weight 0.5-0.6

CFG Scale - 5.5

Eta noise seed delta 31337


Use Abyssorangemix3aom3_aom3a3.safetensors With these negative prompts:
(worst quality, low quality, extra digits:1.4) or (worst quality, low quality:1.4)

items.name: Cima Garahau (Gundam 0083) LoRA
items.description:
Look at her big fleet!

General Info

This LoRA is also trained on the Aurora model from Luna (https://civitai.com/models/40199/aurora) and the results are pretty good! It does a decent job at generating different style images of Cima Garahau from Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory. Most of the sample images have been generated with Aurora too, a few have been generated using Fidelity too.

Usage

The model has been trained using Kohya so you probably want to use it in the same way as you use other Kohya models. If you are Using A1111's Webui you want to move the file into the models>Lora directory. Make sure to use the corresponding trigger words to get the expected results. Also i recommend a LoRA weight of around 0.8.
